{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1707,"text":"People back home call me a heckler,"},{"time":4596,"text":"a troublemaker, an irritant,"},{"time":7313,"text":"a rebel, an activist,"},{"time":9983,"text":"the voice of the people."},{"time":11840,"text":"But that wasn't always me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":14650,"text":"Growing up, I had a nickname."},{"time":16182,"text":"They used to call me Softy,"},{"time":18502,"text":"meaning the soft, harmless boy."},{"time":21755,"text":"Like every other human being,\nI avoided trouble."},{"time":24495,"text":"In my childhood, they taught me silence."},{"time":26538,"text":"Don't argue, do as you're told."},{"time":28340,"text":"In Sunday school, they taught me\ndon't confront, don't argue,"},{"time":32272,"text":"even if you're right,\nturn the other cheek."}]},{"cues":[{"time":35585,"text":"This was reinforced\nby the political climate of the time."},{"time":40182,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":43783,"text":"Kenya is a country\nwhere you are guilty"},{"time":45592,"text":"until proven rich."},{"time":48239,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":50984,"text":"Kenya's poor are five times more likely"},{"time":53726,"text":"to be shot dead by the police\nwho are meant to protect them"},{"time":56650,"text":"than by criminals."},{"time":58298,"text":"This was reinforced\nby the political climate of the day."},{"time":60945,"text":"We had a president,\nMoi, who was a dictator."},{"time":63894,"text":"He ruled the country with an iron fist,"},{"time":66100,"text":"and anyone who dared\nquestion his authority"},{"time":68538,"text":"was arrested, tortured,\njailed or even killed."},{"time":73507,"text":"That meant that people were taught\nto be smart cowards, stay out of trouble."},{"time":77431,"text":"Being a coward was not an insult."},{"time":79474,"text":"Being a coward was a compliment."},{"time":81401,"text":"We used to be told that a coward\ngoes home to his mother."},{"time":84559,"text":"What that meant: that if you stayed\nout of trouble you're going to stay alive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":88320,"text":"I used to question this advice,"},{"time":90260,"text":"and eight years ago\nwe had an election in Kenya,"},{"time":93082,"text":"and the results were violently disputed."},{"time":95565,"text":"What followed that election\nwas terrible violence, rape,"},{"time":100302,"text":"and the killing of over 1,000 people."},{"time":104239,"text":"My work was to document the violence."},{"time":107360,"text":"As a photographer,\nI took thousands of images,"},{"time":110216,"text":"and after two months,"},{"time":112283,"text":"the two politicians came together,\nhad a cup of tea,"},{"time":117158,"text":"signed a peace agreement,\nand the country moved on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":120595,"text":"I was a very disturbed man\nbecause I saw the violence firsthand."},{"time":124124,"text":"I saw the killings.\nI saw the displacement."},{"time":127730,"text":"I met women who had been raped,\nand it disturbed me,"},{"time":130811,"text":"but the country never spoke about it."},{"time":132855,"text":"We pretended. We all became smart cowards."},{"time":135339,"text":"We decided to stay out of trouble\nand not talk about it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":138938,"text":"Ten months later, I quit my job.\nI said I could not stand it anymore."},{"time":142235,"text":"After quitting my job,\nI decided to organize my friends"},{"time":144830,"text":"to speak about\nthe violence in the country,"},{"time":146850,"text":"to speak about the state of the nation,"},{"time":148714,"text":"and June 1, 2009 was the day\nthat we were meant to go to the stadium"},{"time":152830,"text":"and try and get the president's attention."},{"time":154889,"text":"It's a national holiday,"},{"time":156329,"text":"it's broadcast across the country,"},{"time":157978,"text":"and I showed up at the stadium."},{"time":161386,"text":"My friends did not show up."},{"time":164380,"text":"I found myself alone,"},{"time":167753,"text":"and I didn't know what to do."},{"time":170280,"text":"I was scared,"},{"time":171695,"text":"but I knew very well\nthat that particular day,"},{"time":173865,"text":"I had to make a decision."},{"time":175086,"text":"Was I able to live as a coward,\nlike everyone else,"},{"time":177509,"text":"or was I going to make a stand?"},{"time":179107,"text":"And when the president stood up to speak,"},{"time":181313,"text":"I found myself on my feet\nshouting at the president,"},{"time":185920,"text":"telling him to remember\nthe post-election violence victims,"},{"time":189114,"text":"to stop the corruption."},{"time":191390,"text":"And suddenly, out of nowhere,"},{"time":193595,"text":"the police pounced on me\nlike hungry lions."},{"time":196707,"text":"They held my mouth"},{"time":198564,"text":"and dragged me out of the stadium,"},{"time":200491,"text":"where they thoroughly beat me up\nand locked me up in jail."},{"time":205112,"text":"I spent that night in\na cold cement floor in the jail,"},{"time":211870,"text":"and that got me thinking."},{"time":214518,"text":"What was making me feel this way?"},{"time":216389,"text":"My friends and family thought\nI was crazy because of what I did,"},{"time":219554,"text":"and the images that I took\nwere disturbing my life."},{"time":224568,"text":"The images that I took\nwere just a number to many Kenyans."},{"time":227518,"text":"Most Kenyans did not see the violence."},{"time":229465,"text":"It was a story to them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":231160,"text":"And so I decided to actually\nstart a street exhibition"},{"time":233947,"text":"to show the images of the violence\nacross the country"},{"time":236733,"text":"and get people talking about it."},{"time":238707,"text":"We traveled the country\nand showed the images,"},{"time":241516,"text":"and this was a journey that has started me\nto the activist path,"},{"time":244999,"text":"where I decided to become silent no more,"},{"time":247716,"text":"to talk about those things."},{"time":249914,"text":"We traveled, and our general site\nfrom our street exhibit"},{"time":253564,"text":"became for political graffiti\nabout the situation in the country,"},{"time":258362,"text":"talking about corruption, bad leadership."},{"time":261120,"text":"We have even done symbolic burials."},{"time":264900,"text":"We have delivered live pigs\nto Kenya's parliament"},{"time":268882,"text":"as a symbol of our politicians' greed."},{"time":270810,"text":"It has been done in Uganda\nand other countries,"},{"time":273041,"text":"and what is most powerful is that\nthe images have been picked by the media"},{"time":276550,"text":"and amplified across the country,\nacross the continent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":279586,"text":"Where I used to stand up alone\nseven years ago,"},{"time":282233,"text":"now I belong to a community\nof many people who stand up with me."},{"time":285259,"text":"I am no longer alone when I stand up\nto speak about these things."},{"time":290177,"text":"I belong to a group of young people\nwho are passionate about the country,"},{"time":294350,"text":"who want to bring about change,"},{"time":296200,"text":"and they're no longer afraid,\nand they're no longer smart cowards."},{"time":301744,"text":"So that was my story."},{"time":306242,"text":"That day in the stadium,"},{"time":308840,"text":"I stood up as a smart coward."},{"time":311327,"text":"By that one action, I said goodbye\nto the 24 years living as a coward."}]},{"cues":[{"time":316574,"text":"There are two most powerful\ndays in your life:"},{"time":319616,"text":"the day you're born,\nand the day you discover why."},{"time":324771,"text":"That day standing up in that stadium\nshouting at the President,"},{"time":328015,"text":"I discovered why I was truly born,"},{"time":331295,"text":"that I would no longer be silent\nin the face of injustice."},{"time":335776,"text":"Do you know why you were born?"},{"time":339700,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":341535,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":348524,"text":"Tom Rielly: It's an amazing story."},{"time":351031,"text":"I just want to ask you\na couple quick questions."},{"time":353587,"text":"So PAWA254:"},{"time":355907,"text":"you've created a studio, a place\nwhere young people can go"},{"time":360220,"text":"and harness the power of digital media"},{"time":362176,"text":"to do some of this action."},{"time":364687,"text":"What's happening now with PAWA?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":366564,"text":"Boniface Mwangi: So we have \nthis community of filmmakers,"},{"time":369347,"text":"graffiti artists, musicians,\nand when there's an issue in the country,"},{"time":372710,"text":"we come together, we brainstorm,\nand take up on that issue."},{"time":375511,"text":"So our most powerful tool is art,"},{"time":377567,"text":"because we live in a very busy world\nwhere people are so busy in their life,"},{"time":381398,"text":"and they don't have time to read."},{"time":383465,"text":"So we package our activism\nand we package our message in art."},{"time":387598,"text":"So from the music, the graffiti, \nthe art, that's what we do."},{"time":393557,"text":"Can I say one more thing?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":395585,"text":"TR: Yeah, of course. (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":397466,"text":"BM: In spite of being arrested,\nbeaten up, threatened,"},{"time":400101,"text":"the moment I discovered my voice,"},{"time":401814,"text":"that I could actually stand up\nfor what I really believed in,"},{"time":404710,"text":"I'm no longer afraid."},{"time":405748,"text":"I used to be called softy,\nbut I'm no longer softy,"},{"time":408490,"text":"because I discovered who I really am,\nas in, that's what I want to do,"},{"time":411891,"text":"and there's such beauty in doing that."},{"time":414927,"text":"There's nothing as powerful as that,\nknowing that I'm meant to do this,"},{"time":418316,"text":"because you don't get scared,\nyou just continue living your life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":421463,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":423649,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}